nodes.bodyText:
You could keep it as a set, using newSetFromMap():




        Suggested change











                private final Map<String, Thread> binaryLogClientThreads = new ConcurrentHashMap<>(2);



                private final Map<String, Thread> binaryLogClientThreads = Collections.newSetFromMap(new ConcurrentHashMap<>(3));






Also changed the initial size, as 2 wouldn't be enough to hold two elements actually without a resize when using the default load factor. Not that it makes any difference (I'd just call the parameterless constructor), but if we give a size explicitly, it should be large enough.

